#{\footnote TBOX}
{\f1\fs20 A textbox is an area on the screen which allows data to be entered into it or displays data.\par}
{\page}

#{\footnote LBOX}
{\f1\fs20 A listbox is similar to a textbox, except that it has more than one line.\par}
{\page}

#{\footnote DBOX}
{\f1\fs20 A drop-down box is similar to a textbox, except that allows the user to select a value from a list.\par}
{\page}

#{\footnote DIABOX}
{\f1\fs20 A dialog box is a new window which pops up, usually to ask the user for information.\par}
{\page}

#{\footnote BUTTON}
{\f1\fs20 A button is an area on the screen which performs a specific function when the mouse is clicked on it.\par}
{\page}
#{\footnote TOOLBAR}
{\f1\fs20 A toolbar is an area on the screen which contains various {\ul buttons}{\v BUTTON} whick perform an action.\par}
{\page}



